# Cloudflare Pages reads this file automatically and applies these
# headers at the edge, on top of whatever the browser itself does.
#
# Why this file exists: sw.js already bumps its CACHE version and uses
# skipWaiting()/clients.claim() (see sw.js) so the browser SHOULD always
# pick up a new release. But that only works if the browser's check for
# "did sw.js change?" actually reaches a fresh copy of sw.js. If
# Cloudflare's CDN is caching sw.js at the edge with its default/long
# caching rules, the browser's update check can get served that same
# stale cached copy of sw.js indefinitely — no byte difference is ever
# seen, so no update is ever detected, no matter how many times the
# CACHE constant inside it gets bumped. This forces the CDN itself to
# never cache sw.js, so every check reaches the real, current file.
#
# index.html is included for the same reason: it's the very first thing
# loaded, and if the CDN serves an old cached copy of it, the browser
# never even sees the updated <script> tags referencing newer files.

/sw.js
  Cache-Control: no-cache, no-store, must-revalidate

/index.html
  Cache-Control: no-cache, no-store, must-revalidate

/
  Cache-Control: no-cache, no-store, must-revalidate
